    • staffEditCamp

      public void staffEditCamp(Camp camp, List<Camp> campList)
      UI interface for a Staff to walk through editing a camp.
      The Staff to select a category and then the value to change it to.
      Calls CampEdit.TryEditCamp() first then does CampEdit.DoEditCamp() if the changes are deemed legal
      The following parameters can be edited
      Camp Name
      Venue
      Description
      Maximum Slots (Can't change below current signups)
      Maximum Committee Slots (Can't change below current Committee count)
      Start Date (Can't change if there are signups, or to be before Registration End or after End Date)
      End Date (Can't change if there are signups, or to be before Registration End or before Start Date)
      Registration End Date (Can't change if there are signups, or to be after Start Date or after End Date)
      Set Visibility (Can't turn off if any signups)
      Delete Camp (Can't delete if any signups)
      Parameters:
      camp - Camp to be edited
      campList - List of all camps to save program state.

    • createCamp

      public void createCamp(List<Camp> campList)
      UI interface for a Staff to walk through creating a camp.
      Each input, if relevant will be handed to the relevant InputHelper method to validate.
      The following parameters to be filled in:
      Camp Name
      Faculty-only or Open to all?
      Venue
      Description
      Maximum Slots
      Maximum Committee Slots
      Start Date
      End Date
      Registration End Date
      Set Visibility
      Parameters:
      campList - List of all Camp objects to save the program state

    • adminMenu

      default void adminMenu(List<Camp> campList, User activeUser, List<Suggestion> suggestionList, List<Enquiry> enquiryList)
      This method displays and resolves the options for the Admin menu.
      In the main CAMs menu, a check must be done to ensure Student accounts don't call for this method.
      This menu behaves differently based on whether the ActiveUser is a Staff or a StudentCommittee.
      Parameters:
      campList - List of all Camps. Used in parsing camps that are available for the user to perform admin actions on.
      activeUser - User object of the active user.
      suggestionList - List of all Suggestions. Used to save the state of Suggestions.
      enquiryList - List of all Enquiries. Used to save the state of Enquiries.
